Summer 2020: IDK these; deal with later? LL: B. auritus-australis is an accepted name (see WoRMS); AF what's with these, that's no sort of formal taxonomy i'm used to. Winter 2021: From David Lazarus: Best call this 'Euchitonia elegans/furcata group’  for now. It is in NSB at the moment as a valid taxon [id 2004045]. Some people believe furcata and elegans can be distinguished but others do not understand how.  So currently ‘elegans’ and ‘furcata’ by themselves are given as synonyms for the ‘group’ version in NSB.  Not elegan[t]\s but that’s what we’ve got.
